Package: RangeR
Title: Calculating the range for electric vehicles based on various components
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Arthur", "Dreher", "arthur.dreher@stud-mail.uni-wuerzburg.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Calculates and displays the range of electric vehicles (EVs)
    based on topographic and environmental factors. Includes a database of 
    over 650 modern EV models, with functionality to add custom vehicles 
    via 'add_custom_ev'. Provides 'range_buffer_simple' for simple range 
    estimates considering battery level and ambient temperature. Offers a 
    sophisticated 'calc_ev_topo_buffer' function that downloads Digital 
    Elevation Models (DEMs) and charging network data to compute realistic, 
    topography-aware range buffers. Results can be visualized on an 
    interactive map showing non-uniform range polygons.
